Thanksgiving Gifts: 2020 Gifts That Say Thanks

Every year, the holidays are a time for gift giving, without a doubt. This year, it seems like we have even more to be thankful for, and even more of a reason to be thankful. 

When looking for a gift to say thank you to the special people in your life, you can never go wrong with a gift of sweets, or by pairing sweets with other gifts. 

The Nuttery NY is thankful to be able to provide you with a large selection of treats to choose from this year! From holiday chocolate pies to gift boxes filled with chocolate covered oreos here are some ideas catered to the people you’ll likely be gifting to this holiday season.


What to Give Your Thanksgiving Host



This Thanksgiving, don’t be the person that brings the fruitcake no one eats and everyone makes fun of. Instead, bring a sweet treat that everyone will be sure to enjoy. We have a few delicious treats sure to make you the hit of any Thanksgiving get-together. 


Chocolate Logs 

To start,chocolate logs make an excellent gift for any Thanksgiving host. The best news: they come in a variety of different flavors and patterns, which means there is a chocolate log for any holiday event! They also make great centerpieces, and can serve between 10 and 30 people. Each log is Kosher Certified, as well, so everyone can enjoy them!

Chocolate praline  is a favorite, not only because of its festive, holiday flavor, but also the beautiful white chocolate lace pattern. It is made out of the richest, creamiest chocolate we make, and comes on a beautiful, mahogany wooden tray for serving. It’s truly an elegant centerpiece that will elicit “oohs” and “aahs” not only from your Thanksgiving host, but from everyone else at the table as well.

Chocolate peanut butter is a classic option and flavor combination, and it comes with a lace pattern also made out of chocolate. Peanut butter is a favorite of so many people, young and old alike, and this tasty log combines that with creamy, rich, thick chocolate.

Chocolate pistachio is a less traditional option, which is part of its allure! It has a unique, beautiful white chocolate pattern. The pistachio is mixed right in with the Parve chocolate on the inside of the log, making for a delicious yet fun holiday treat.

Halvah Zebra logs are one more, super unique option to bring to Thanksgiving. With their rich, sesame flavor, they taste just as good (if not better!) than they look. It’s hard to describe the flavor to someone who hasn’t experienced it, but it’s exotic while still tasting smooth and buttery.

Chocolate Tray 

If chocolate logs aren’t your thing, consider a specialized Thanksgiving gift tray. The tray is visually stunning and fall appropriate, served on a light, wooden tray and decorated with an autumn orange colored ribbon with the word “thankful” on it. And every guest at the event will be thankful too, as the gift tray is filled with parve chocolates.

The Thanksgiving gift tray features a two tone roll, which is essentially a white chocolate truffle in log form. It is decorated with delicious dark chocolate details and absolutely just melts in the mouth. It also comes stocked with viennese crunch, a bite size candy made of caramel and chocolate and covered in nuts. In addition, there are jelly rings (Kosher gummies covered in dark chocolate), kava crunch (another delicious candy), cashew patties (freshly roasted cashews clustered together with a creamy, caramel glaze and drizzled with dark chocolate), moccachino (coffee flavored candies), and hazelicious (delicious hazelnut fudge covered in dark chocolate). 

Candy and Nut Tray

If that sounds like too much chocolate for you, we also offer a four section Thanksgiving gift tray that substitutes some of the candy with some of our finest speciality nuts. It’s a sweet and salty holiday treat everyone will enjoy!When you bring any one of our above mentioned specialty gourmet treats to Thanksgiving, your holiday host will be extra thankful for you this year. They also let you show how thankful you are for having them host! If you want to really express your gratitude, help them with the clean up. 

What to Give Your Parents on Thanksgiving

If you’re going home for the holidays, you likely already know the struggle associated with finding and bringing your parents the perfect Thanksgiving gift. Your parents have done so much for you in your life, and it’s only natural to want to show them how thankful you are for them. 

We’re here to help with that with some gift ideas for your parents this Thanksgiving. For starters, parents always love gifts that remind them that you’re always going to be their loving child, which is why personalization can never go wrong.


The best news is that, especially these days, you can personalize just about anything! It all depends on what your parents are into and what you think they would use frequently.

Personalized Picture Frame with an Old Family Photo 

One of the best gift ideas that we can think of is a personalized picture frame filled with an old, restored family photo. While this may take a little time and research, the look on your parents face when they see it is worth more than gold. Parents love the nostalgia factor, and you’ll love knowing you’ve made your parents incredibly happy. It’s definitely something to be thankful for.

Matching Mugs and Sweet Treats 

Matching mugs for your mom and dad are also a great holiday gift option. You can even personalize them further by having their pictures printed directly on them (for an extra special gift idea, use childhood photos of either them or yourself and other siblings). 

Pair the photo mugs with a box of chocolates, like the Nuttery Signature Chocolate Box or the tart box and it will be a gift they’re sure to love. We think that the tarts are a particularly good choice, as each of the three is handmade, come in a classy box, and pair perfectly with a nice, hot cup of coffee. If they share with you, you’ll have something to be extra thankful for too!


Gifts for Your Employees on Thanksgiving

If you have employees that you need to buy for this Thanksgiving but aren’t sure where to start, we’re here to help make it as easy on you as possible. 


Corporate Confection Boxes 

Consider giving them a classic corporate holiday gift box. 

Each box is actually an impressive two tiers, with an attractive art deco pattern. Each level is full of a sweet array of gourmet treats, meant to show your sweet, sweet appreciation. The gift box is full of dried apricot and pineapple tidbits, craisins, dried kiwi, cookie poppers, sweet peanuts, coffee candies, and salted cashews, each in their own separate gift boxes. They are compact and will show your employees just how thankful you are for them this holiday season. It has also shown to boost morale, and that’s something you can be thankful for too! For smaller companies that can afford a little heftier holiday gift box for their employees, this 9 section corporate gift box is perfect. Each delicious section has its own tasty uniqueness - crispies, butter softies, hazelnut cigars, raspberry fruit, nut mix, BBQ pistachios, sweet peanuts, salted cashews,and  salted almonds. Any employee would be thrilled to receive this gift box for any occasion, and when it’s meant to show how thankful you are for them it’s even more special. And it just looks impressive!


Smaller Gifts for Other People You’re Thankful For
 

Just because they’re not your family doesn’t mean you can’t treat them like they are. This holiday season, show your appreciation to the other people in your life that you’re thankful for by giving them smaller, thoughtful gifts meant to show just how much you care. Gifts like the ones we’re featuring are perfect for people like teachers, friends, postal workers, and anyone else that you’d like to thank for whatever joy or convenience they bring to your life. It’s a nice, inexpensive way to show them how important they are to you.


Chocolate Covered Oreos 

One of our favorites are these classic gift boxes filled with chocolate covered oreos. The festively colored gift boxes are covered in a seasonal, fall pattern, and the chocolate covered oreos inside are not only tasty but also certified kosher! They can even be personalized with a logo for an extra special touch.

Holiday Chocolate Pie 

If you need a gift to bring over to your neighbors, give to your coworkers, or bring to your church group or temple holiday event, consider the holiday chocolate pie. The pie is made out of the most rich, decadent, creamy praline chocolate that we make, and decorated by hand with festively colored chocolate decorations (in red and green). Each pie comes on its own beautiful, round tray that you won’t have to worry about bringing home with you. These pies make for the perfect holiday centerpiece, no matter wherever you have to go this holiday season. It’ll impress everyone, nearly guaranteed. 


No matter what you give to show how thankful you are this holiday season, if you give a gift with love and care behind it, it’s obvious. Have a blessed and happy Thanksgiving!
